description: In a new study of politicians' personalities, humor, charm and raw courage are listed among the most important character traits for successful leaders.
title: Study of key characteristics of UK politicians reveals 'ambition, narcissism, genuine idealism' among common traits

description: Scientists have revealed fossils of a giant salamanderlike beast with sharp fangs that ruled waters before the first dinosaurs arrived.
title: Fossils show huge salamanderlike predator with sharp fangs existed before the dinosaurs

description: Growing populations and housing shortages are affecting cities worldwide, including in Australia. It's driving them to adopt high-density development near public transport hubs instead of endless suburban sprawl on city fringes.
title: How to ensure higher-density housing developments still have enough space for residents' recreation needs

description: The first big moment on election night in the UK, after polls close, happens at 10pm sharp. This is when the exit poll is released and the media commentary floodgates are reopened after a day of media silence, according to broadcasting rules.
title: The exit poll: What is it, how is it made and how did it become such an accurate prediction of election results?

description: Humanity has made great strides in recent decades: air is cleaner; poverty, deforestation and childhood mortality have fallen; gasoline cars—and maybe coal—are on the way out.
title: 'Not the end of the world', says data scientist on the big issues

description: The crew of a NASA mission to Mars emerged from their craft after a yearlong voyage that never left Earth.
title: Crew of NASA's earthbound simulated Mars habitat emerge after a year
